1 A Little Survey

Here are just a few questions so I can get to know you and so you can get practice submitting an assignment in Canvas. For each question, insert your answer underneath. Make sure each answer is at the minimum a complete sentence with correctly spelled words and correct puncuation. Half the points in this assignment depend on your picture and name being correct!! Be sure to put your photo in the AAA_Owner_Info folder and call it My_photo.jpg after first renaming the current one to Koala.jpg .

1.1 Where are you now?

What row are you in, front,middle or back? Do you usually choose a similiar row in other classes? What is the computer number where you are sitting? How on a scale of 1 to 10 (1=low, 10=high) How you feel about periodic seat re-assignment, say how and why. Teams, have you ever worked on one in a class setting?

1.1.1 my answer

I typically sit in the back rows of my classes if given the opportunity. I tend to stay back and raise my concerns with the class in private.
My computer number is 71831.
I feel at about a 5 for seat re-assignment. It does not bother me in the slgihtest so I am neutral on the matter
I have worked with teams throughout high school and college. It does not bother me to do so and I rate it at about a 5.

1.2 Others and You?

What name do you prefer to be called by your classmates and instructor, if your buddys call you something but you want me to call you something else - what would that be?

1.2.1 my answer

I don’t really have any prefered name to be called in class. People either call me Logan or Martinez. Whichever one you want to use is fine by me. I’ll respond.

1.3 Aspirations?

What do you want to achieve in life? What college subject do you think would be of the greatest interest to you? What degree or certificate are you trying to achieve?

1.3.1 my answer

I want to do international translation in the future. Maybe build my retirement house. Nothing too crazy. My current major is Japanese linguistis at UCSC. For now I am taking courses at AVC due to scheduling conflicts.

1.4 Past adventures?

Have you ever gone to foreign countries, if so which ones, if not Where might you go in the future? Have you ever been in the military, if so which branch, if not which branch would you choose if you got drafted, and why?

1.4.1 my answer

I have been to Mexico, France, and Japan. They were wonderful experiences. And I could either speak with the locals or understand what was written down in every trip, so they were extra interesting. I would love to visit Russia and Germany
I have never been in the military, but in high school I wanted to enlist. If I got drafter I think the marines would be fun. I like the brotherhood that comes with that branch because it is forged through hardships and trials.

1.5 Why are you taking Math 115?

What grade do you need to attain in stats to not upset your future plans, What is your plan?

1.5.1 my answer

I am taking 115 becuase I could not understand the statistics courses offered to me at UCSC.I simply need to pass this class. My plan is to pass this, then finish my degree next year, graduate, then go overseas to teach or translate.

1.6 Homework Help and Getting around?

On a scale of 1 to 10, where 1 is a total dummy (doesn’t know a mouse from a keyboard) and 10 is a complete geek (knows computer stuff in and out) How do you rate yourself? Do you have a computer you can use at home? If so, what kind is it (windows, Apple, Linux)? Do you have internet access at home?
How do you get to class? Are there issues that limit when you can be at the college?Where and when did you attend high school? Do you currently have a job?

1.6.1 my answer

I rate myself at aboout a 6.5 on computer stuff. I kn ow enoughto be able to troubleshoot and emulate but not enough to write a program or diagnose problems. I have a pc at home that I can use. It is a windows computer with internet access.
I drive to class. I need to get a parking permit but for now I drive. I have a full time job that I do during the days and then come here at night. The only issue is a week in may that I need to be in South Dakota for a wedding. I attended high school at Highland HS from 2011 to 2015.
